Former BBC Political Editor Nick Robinson interviews retired
football manager Alex Ferguson, who not only led Manchester United
to pick up every domestic football trophy available during the
course of his 26-year premiership, but also transformed the team
into a multi-million pound global business. In a candid interview
with Nick, Sir Alex reveals how he managed to stay at the top of his
profession for so long, and shares crucial tips on motivating,
disciplining and inspiring people. He also offers his unique
perspective on leadership - one that has come to find resonance
beyond the world of football. Includes contributions by Cristiano
Ronaldo, Tony Blair, Alan Sugar, Ryan Giggs, Rio Ferdinand, Jose
Mourinho and Professor Anita Elberse.
